# expansion.log — Inflationary epoch event log
# Duration: ~10⁻³² seconds
# This is the fastest and most consequential process
# in the history of the universe.

[10⁻³⁶s] INFLATION START
  trigger: false_vacuum_decay
  driver: inflaton_field
  initial_size: 10⁻²⁶ m (sub-subatomic)
  expansion_rate: exponential (doubling every 10⁻³⁷s)

[10⁻³⁶s + ε] QUANTUM FLUCTUATIONS FROZEN
  status: Quantum fluctuations in the inflaton field
          are stretched to macroscopic scales.
  consequence: These become the seeds of all future structure —
               galaxies, galaxy clusters, cosmic web.
  note: The largest structures in the universe originate
        from the smallest quantum uncertainties.
        Scale invariance of the power spectrum confirms this.

[10⁻³⁵s] HORIZON PROBLEM RESOLVED
  status: Regions now causally disconnected were in contact
          before inflation. This explains why the CMB
          temperature is uniform to 1 part in 100,000
          across the entire sky.

[10⁻³⁴s] FLATNESS ACHIEVED
  status: Spatial curvature driven to Ω ≈ 1.000 ± 0.001
  note: Without inflation, fine-tuning of initial conditions
        to 1 part in 10⁶⁰ would be required.
        Inflation makes flatness natural, not miraculous.

[10⁻³³s] MONOPOLE DILUTION
  status: Magnetic monopoles (predicted by GUT) diluted
          to ≤ 1 per observable universe.
  note: This is why we have never detected one.

[10⁻³²s] INFLATION END — REHEATING
  status: Inflaton field decays into Standard Model particles.
  temperature: ~10²⁷ K
  energy: Converted from inflaton potential to particle kinetic energy.
  result: Hot, dense, uniform plasma ready for standard Big Bang nucleosynthesis.

[POST-INFLATION SUMMARY]
  total_expansion: ≥ 10²⁶× (possibly 10¹⁰⁰⁰⁰⁰×)
  duration: ~10⁻³² seconds
  universe_size_after: >> observable universe today
  key_achievement: Turned quantum noise into cosmic structure
  open_questions:
    - What is the inflaton field?
    - Did inflation happen exactly once, or is it eternal?
    - Is our observable universe one bubble in an infinite multiverse?
